snippet.textDisplay: #postmortem i’m not sure how many years this happened for, but for many years, on edgar allan poe’s birthday, someone (the “poe toaster”) would leave roses and cognac at his grave. the person was never revealed, even though people would go out on poe’s birthday and wait for the person to leave the roses and cognac. they never saw the person but the items still were left at the grave. the tradition came to an abrupt stop and people are unsure why.
